-- Vodafone CEO says open to Liberty Global deal -Bloomberg
-- By Tricia Wright
-- Thu Sep 11, 2014 09:51AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 11 (Reuters) - Network operator Vodafone's <VOD.L> chief executive has reportedly said he is open to a deal with cable group Liberty Global <LBTYA.O> at the right price, traders said, citing a report posted on Bloomberg terminals.

Shares in Vodafone were down 1.1 percent at 202.80 pence by 1336 GMT, well below a session high of 206.45 pence, with traders attributing the fall to the reported comments. "[Vodafone] CEO Vittorio Colao says co. is open to Liberty Global deal at the right price," the report, published on Bloomberg terminals, said.